    <briefdescription>
<para>Local oscillator: NCO + 2^16 sin/cos LUT → CF32 phasors. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The 32-bit phase accumulator drives a static 65536-entry float sine LUT. The top 16 bits of the phase select the LUT index; a quarter-cycle offset (LUT_QTR = 16384) converts sin to cos without extra storage:</para>
<para>idx = phase &gt;&gt; 16 out(i) = cos(θ) + j·sin(θ) = lut((idx + LUT_QTR) &amp; 0xFFFF) + j·lut(idx)</para>
<para>Output is emitted BEFORE the phase is incremented (same convention as NCO).</para>
<para>The 16-bit phase truncation gives ~96 dBc SFDR.</para>
<para>Lifecycle: lo_create → (steps / reset)* → lo_destroy</para>
<para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="structlo__state__t" kindref="compound">lo_state_t</ref><sp/>*lo<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="lo__core_8h_1a29d475585a62a2f1dd3e83217d727d80" kindref="member">lo_create</ref>(0.25);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="keywordtype">float</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>complex<sp/>out[4];</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="lo__core_8h_1a343680be8b9bdec6c26498bc81f34269" kindref="member">lo_steps</ref>(lo,<sp/>4,<sp/>out);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>out<sp/>≈<sp/>{<sp/>1+0j,<sp/>0+1j,<sp/>-1+0j,<sp/>0-1j<sp/>}</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="lo__core_8h_1ac33a2e59bd8c4bc1b18b3f982c494da5" kindref="member">lo_destroy</ref>(lo);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
    </detaileddescription>
